    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Workup dependent on presentation, considerations include:\nCBC, BMP, Mg/Phos\nLow threshold for infectious workup, including viral/fungal studies\nTacrolimus, cyclosporine levels\nECG\nPatient’s native sinus node often preserved\n→ two P waves on ECG\ndonor P wave will be in 1:1 relationship with QRS, native P wave has independent rhythm\nCXR\nMay have relative \"cardiomegaly\" if donor was much larger than recipient\nCT Chest\nMay be required to diagnose PE, hypoxemia, pneumonia\nEchocardiography\nConsider if signs/symptoms of heart failure",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "ECG",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/ECG"
        },
        {
          "text": "CXR",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/CXR"
        },
        {
          "text": "Echocardiography",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Echocardiography"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management_Considerations": {
      "text": "Consult/discuss with transplant team\nRejection\nDiagnosed by biopsy\nDo not treat if stable, as steroids will muddy biopsy results\nMethylprednisolone\n1g IV if in extremis\nDysrhythmias\nBradycardia\nwill ‘’’NOT’’’ respond to atropine due to denervation\ntransplant patients with symptomatic bradycardia may respond to isoproterenol 1 μg/min, titrated slowly to max 4 μg/min\nTransplant patients may be overly sensitive to adverse effects from\nadenosine\nSinus node dysfunction usually requires pacemaker placement\nSee\nImmunocompromised antibiotics",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Methylprednisolone",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Methylprednisolone"
        },
